{"name":"Die Hard","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Through either mental resolve or sheer stubbornness, the Acolyte refuses to fall. When this character would suffer a level of Fatigue due to the Blood Loss condition, he makes a Challenging (+0) Willpower test; if he succeeds, he does not suffer a level of Fatigue.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 40","aptitudes":"Willpower, Defence","benefit":"Test Willpower to avoid Fatigue from Blood Loss.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"057gufintNuvkOTm"}
{"name":"Unarmed Specialist","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>After extensive training, the Acolyte has made his body as dangerous as any Munitorum-issued weapon. He gains the Deadly Natural Weapon trait (see page 135), and counts as armed even when facing weapon-wielding opponents while barehanded. While fighting barehanded, he can also re-roll the damage he inflicts.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 35, Ambidextrous, Weapon Skill 35","aptitudes":"Strength, Offence","benefit":"When fighting unarmed, attacks hit as Deadly Natural Weapons and user can re-roll damage.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"1FLmKE91nSxQ69X6"}
{"name":"Contact Network","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Acolytes rely on a web of relationships, favours, debts, and obligations that can range from within a hab-block to spanning an entire system. Developing and exploiting this network properly allows them to gain access to weapons, travel berths, personnel, and other resources when needed; those who maximise their connections can ensure they are well-armed and well-prepared as they face a new heresy. An Acolyte with this talent can use his Fellowship characteristic in place of his Influence when making Requisition tests (see page 142).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Cover-Up, Intelligence 35","aptitudes":"Fellowship, Leadership","benefit":"Use Fellowship instead of Influence for Requisition tests.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"1ujSIV0kDju3DaFY"}
{"name":"Taited Psyker","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Though all psykers draw their power from the Warp, the Scholastica Psykana teaches that the Warp is something to fear. Some psykers ignore these warnings, whether wyrds who escaped the Black Ships, scholars of malefic lore, or even sanctioned psykers fallen from grace. Such tainted psykers embrace the true potential the Warp ofers, and even heed its denizens&rsquo; whispered promises of greater power.</p>\n<p>When making a Focus Power test, the character may gain a number of Corruption points up to his psy rating. For each point he gains in this way, he gains a +10 bonus to the Focus Power test but adds +5 to rolls on Table 6&ndash;2: Psychic Phenomena (see page 196 of the DARK HERESY Core Rulebook).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Psy rating, Rank 2 (Trained) in Psyniscience skill, 10 Corruption points","aptitudes":"Knowledge, Psyker","benefit":"gain boni on focus power for corruption","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"2mKmN27bUBnI10hO"}
{"name":"Hardy","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s constitution allows him to rebound quickly from shock or injury. When undergoing medical treatment or healing from injuries, he always recovers damage as if Lightly Damaged, regardless of the level of damage he sustained.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Toughness 40","aptitudes":"Toughness, Defence","benefit":"Character always heals as if Lightly Damaged.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"3f5q0VDzfSGlYaJC"}
{"name":"Bulging Biceps","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Whereas a weaker man might be sent flying by the recoil of a heavy weapon, this Acolyte&rsquo;s strong physique allows him to remain standing. He can fire a heavy weapon using Semi-Auto Burst or Full Auto Burst without bracing the weapon, and does not suffer the &ndash;30 penalty for failing to brace it. In addition, whenever he uses the Heft special use of the Athletics skill (see page 98) he can add +20 to his Athletics skill test to reflect his powerful musculature.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Strength 45","aptitudes":"Strength, Offence","benefit":"Remove bracing requirement from Heavy weapons.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"5mC2ZQveF1t8H7Em"}
{"name":"Disarm","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte can wrest weapons from his opponents&rsquo; hands through practised technique or brute force. As a Full Action, the character may make an Opposed Weapon Skill test against one target with whom he is engaged. If the Acolyte wins the test, the enemy drops his weapon to the ground. Should the Acolyte score three or more degrees of success, he can take the enemy&rsquo;s weapon from him.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 30","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Defence","benefit":"Force opponent to drop weapon.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"71urezTtQoj8hTRB"}
{"name":"Armour-Monger","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is a skilled armourer, and constantly tinkers and improves his armour, or keeps it in pristine shape by repairing the slightest damage it sustains. With years of training, he has even learned to enhance the protection afforded by his armour and how to use it to its optimum. The character gains an extra amount of Armour points equal to his Intelligence bonus, which he can distribute to any locations that his armour would normally cover, as long as he has at least an hour each day to clean and repair it or make minor modifications. This bonus applies only to armour when the Acolyte is wearing it, as it combines his training with his skill at armoury.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Intelligence 35, Tech-Use, Trade (Armourer)","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Tech","benefit":"Increase the efficacy of physical armour.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"8g1EIcZMzvvuYVz1"}
{"name":"Constant Vigilance*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Intelligence, Perception</p>\n<p>From years of surviving ambushes and surprise attacks, the Acolyte is always ready for battle. His subconscious is alert to the slightest footstep or activation of a lasgun pack, and he acts often before he is fully aware of the threat. When this talent is taken, the character selects the Specialisation that matches the prerequisite (Perception or Intelligence) used in purchase. He can use the characteristic that matches that Specialisation when rolling for Initiative instead of his Agility value, and rolls two dice for the roll (picking the highest of the two for his score).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Awareness +10, Intelligence 35 or Perception 35","aptitudes":"Perception, Defence","benefit":"Can use Per or Int instead of Ag for Initiative rolls, and rolls two dice (picking higher) for the result.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"92Rqou5gYQVHHAEW"}
{"name":"Rites of Banishment","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>In battle against the daemonic, the Acolyte ceaselessly intones sacred rites and invocations against the Daemon, calling on the Emperor to cast the abominations back into the Warp. These holy words disrupt the Daemon&rsquo;s hold in the material universe, weakening its malefic form.</p>\n<p>Effect: Once per round as a Half Action, the character may speak the litanies and invocations to disrupt Daemons. Until the beginning of his next turn, Daemons within a distance equal to twice the character&rsquo;s Willpower bonus in meters suffer a &ndash;10 penalty to Willpower tests.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Common Lore (Imperial Creed) +10 or Forbidden Lore (Daemonology)","aptitudes":"Offence, Willpower","benefit":"speak the litanies and Daemons suffer a â€“10 penalty to WP tests","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"98tHMb14907Yk0Ih"}
{"name":"Iron Jaw","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has taken blows from Orks and given back as good as he got, bouncing back from most strikes without ill effects. Whenever this character becomes Stunned, he may make a Challenging (+0) Toughness test as a Free Action to ignore the effects.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Toughness 40","aptitudes":"Toughness, Defence","benefit":"Test Toughness to overcome Stunning.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"A1iWxowpRG1Fs3kR"}
{"name":"Counter Attack","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s lightning ripostes are things of deadly beauty; swift and invisible as the wind. Once per turn, after successfully Parrying an opponent&rsquo;s attack, this character may immediately make a Standard Attack action as a Free Action against that opponent using the weapon with which he Parried. The character suffers a &ndash;20 penalty on the Weapon Skill test for this attack.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 40","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Defence","benefit":"May attack after successful Parry","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"ADnEDc4tjTEwzNxt"}
{"name":"Battle Rage","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Long experience and indomitable will have allowed the character to master the beast within, directing its rage while keeping his head, despite the howling bloodlust in his mind. The Acolyte can Parry while Frenzied, and can re-roll a failed test to snap out of Frenzy or resist entering Frenzy if he so chooses.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Frenzy","aptitudes":"Strength, Defence","benefit":"Parry while frenzied.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"ALl7vYDPKwWnFRvs"}
{"name":"Two-Weapon Wielder","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Intensive training allows the Acolyte to use a weapon in each hand when needed. When armed with two one-handed weapons (ether melee or ranged weapons), after making a Half Action attack (this can be a Single Attack, a Swift Attack, or a Lightning Attack with a melee weapon, or it can be a single shot, semi-auto burst, or full auto burst with a ranged weapon), he can make a single additional Half Action attack following the same restrictions with the other weapon as a Free Action. In effect, this allows him to attack twice in a round, once from each of his weapons. Both of these attacks count as being part of the same Half Action, and both tests made to attack with the weapons suffer a &ndash;20 penalty.</p>\n<p>This talent can be taken twice, each time with a different specialisation (melee or ranged). If he possesses both talents, then he can fight with one melee and one ranged weapon. When this talent is taken with the melee focus it counts as having the Weapon Skill and Finesse aptitudes, and when it is taken with the ranged focus it counts as having the Ballistic Skill and Finesse aptitudes.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Melee, Ranged","benefit":"May fight with two weapons.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"BahaPM33IoxwvEZ0"}
{"name":"Maglev Transcendence","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has learned how to better use his implanted maglev coils, and can hover for a number of minutes equal to 1d10 plus twice his Toughness bonus. He can move his Run speed when making a Half Move action and suffers no damage from falling if the coils are active. Each use drains half the power stored in the coils (therefore he can use the coils twice before recharging them).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Maglev Coils, Mechanicus Implants","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Tech","benefit":"Character can hover for longer periods of time.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"D2MvdjDG86e9ACQ7"}
{"name":"Cover-Up","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Even the slightest whisper of the Inquisition&rsquo;s presence can be enough to scatter suspected heretics and drive cults into hiding. To prevent the growth and spread of rumours, Acolytes use combinations of well-placed bribes, dire threats, and other means to keep their activities as secretive as possible. At the GM&rsquo;s discretion, the character can reduce his Influence to increase his group&rsquo;s Subtlety. For every point of Influence lost in this way, the Acolyte increases his warband&rsquo;s Subtlety by 1d5.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Intelligence 35","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Knowledge","benefit":"Can reduce Influence by 1 to gain 1d5 Subtlety.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"DVpSxK7zO7HVzmTQ"}
{"name":"Witch Finder","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>In order to root out the witch, wyrd, and sorcerer, an Inquisitor or Acolyte must be able to detect and follow the sign and spoor of the psyker. Although some are themselves psykers, or employ the services of such, others train their own senses and mind to detect even the subtlest traces of psychic activity. The character counts as possessing the Psyniscience skill at Rank 1 (Known), even though he is not a psyker. Note that he cannot spend experience to gain additional ranks in the skill.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 2 (Trained) in the Forbidden Lore (Psykers) skill, Willpower 45","aptitudes":"Knowledge, Perception","benefit":"gain  Psyniscience skill at Rank 1","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"EHxVvK0F5AZJjbOd"}
{"name":"Mounted Warrior*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Specialisations: Melee, Ranged</p>\n<p>Hard-won experience fighting from the saddle or seat of a vehicle has trained the Acolyte to adjust for the motion of mounted combat, moving with the vehicle instead of fighting against it. When a character purchases this talent, he selects the specialisation that matches the characteristic prerequisite and aptitude used in purchase. He then reduces any penalty for making corresponding attacks (Melee or Ranged) from a moving vehicle or mount by 10 for each time the talent has been purchased in that specialisation. This applies to both ordinary attack actions and vehicle combat actions, such as Hit and Run.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 2 (Trained) in any Operate skill or Rank 2 (Trained) in Survival skill, Ballistic Skill 30 or Weapon Skill 30","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill or Ballistic Skill, Ofence","benefit":"No penalty for mounted fighting","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"ExoOIKCqxqKesiO7"}
{"name":"Combat Master","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s weapon seems to be everywhere at once, keeping many more opponents at bay in close combat than would seem possible. Opponents fighting him in hand-to-hand combat gain no bonuses for Ganging Up (see page 229).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 30","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Defence","benefit":"Opponents get no bonus for outnumbering the character.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"GBZE2ORI24KDNMCh"}
{"name":"Prosanguine","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Through the Acolyte&rsquo;s iron will, he is able to speed the function of his Autosanguinator. He must spend 10 minutes in meditation and make a Tech-Use test. If he succeeds, he removes 1d5 points of damage. If he rolls a 96 or higher, he loses the ability to use his Autosanguinator for one week.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Autosanguine Implants, Mechanicus Implants","aptitudes":"Toughness, Tech","benefit":"Test to heal 1d5 damage.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"GPsMQ9L29nqeRkmi"}
{"name":"Peer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Any listed in the sidebar The Powers of Askellon</p>\n<p>(see page 126), others at GM&rsquo;s discretion</p>\n<p>The Acolyte knows how to deal with a particular social group or organisation, or even xenos race. He gains a +10 bonus to all Fellowship and Influence tests when interacting with this chosen group, and at the GM&rsquo;s discretion can sometimes call upon them for favours. The GM and player may agree to award this talent when appropriate to the adventure or campaign, though the character must still pay the experience cost for the Talent as normal. This talent can be awarded multiple times for the same group, in which case it should be listed as Peer (X), with X equalling the number of times the talent has been awarded. This can be used to represent groups who particularly like the character and may even be staunch allies. In game terms, the bonus to Fellowship tests increases to +10 times X. Additionally, when the character acquires this talent, he increases his Influence by 1.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Fellowship 30","aptitudes":"Fellowship, Social","benefit":"Character has good reputation amongst chosen group.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"GsANRCes2Mdpeb6G"}
{"name":"Frenzy","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s temper and passion boil just below the surface of his psyche, mostly held in check by his rational mind, but easily released when needed. If he spends one full round fuelling his anger&mdash;by flagellation, drugs, or other means&mdash;on the next round, he goes into an uncontrolled rage, gaining a +10 bonus to Weapon Skill, Strength, Toughness, and Willpower, but suffering a &ndash; 0 penalty to Ballistic Skill, Intelligence, and Fellowship. Note that characteristic penalties are different from characteristic damage (see page 188), and cannot reduce a characteristic below 1. While Frenzied, the character must attack the nearest enemy in melee combat if possible. If he is not engaged with the nearest enemy, he must move towards that enemy and engage it if possible. He will not take obviously suicidal actions such as leaping off a building in order to engage someone on the ground, but he will take any actions that offer a reasonable opportunity to engage in melee with the nearest enemy.</p>\n<p>While Frenzied, he is immune to Fear, Pinning, Stunning effects, and the effects of Fatigue; he cannot Parry, retreat, or flee. He remains Frenzied for the duration of the combat, and cannot use psychic powers while Frenzied. After combat ends, or if there are no more eligible enemy targets for the character to attack, he can make a Willpower test to snap out of his Frenzy. If he fails, he must continue to attack, favouring NPCs over PCs. Each successive round, however, he can make another Willpower test, with a cumulative +10 bonus to return to a stable state of mind and come out of Frenzy. After Frenzying, he cannot Frenzy again for at least an hour, as he recovers his mental and physical strength.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Strength, Offence","benefit":"Enter psychotic rage to gain combat bonuses.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"H5izhTNN7l0r7IDZ"}
{"name":"Hard Target","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Light on his feet, the Acolyte dodges and weaves as he moves, skills learned from long years in the line of fire. When he performs a Charge or Run action, opponents suffer a &ndash;20 penalty to Ballistic Skill tests made to hit him with ranged attacks. This penalty continues until the start of his next turn.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 40","aptitudes":"Agility, Defence","benefit":"â€“20 to hit character when he Charges or Runs.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"HQ53tYoO5EI4IopL"}
{"name":"Archivator","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Whether through years of experience or specialised training, the Acolyte is a master of mining information from the Imperium&rsquo;s countless archives. From delving into deep info-crypts to searching mouldering librarium stacks and deciphering ancient tech-slabs, the Acolyte can uncover knowledge thought long lost. When making a Scholastic Lore or Forbidden Lore test utilising sources of recorded information of any sort, such as cogitators, tomes, info-nets, and data-slates, the character can reroll a failed test once with a &ndash;10 penalty. In addition, tests to perform research or find information in these circumstances take half the usual time.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Int 40","aptitudes":"Knowledge, Perception","benefit":"The Acolyte is a master of mining information from the Imperiumâ€™s countless archives.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"HRkyOA7T98Y07Nik"}
{"name":"Hip Shooting","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s prowess with ranged weapons is such that he can still fire accurately without his eye behind the sights. As a Full Action, he can both move up to his Full Move rate and make a single attack with a ranged weapon. This attack can only be a single shot, and so cannot be a semi- or full-automatic ranged attack for example. Characters with the Two-Weapon Fighting talent can use this talent with Hip Shooting to make two single shots, if they are armed with a ranged weapon in each hand.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 40, Ballistic Skill 40","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Finesse","benefit":"Characters may shoot when moving.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"IwPnmfRJGyRu8F15"}
{"name":"Strong Minded","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s mind acts as a fortress against psychic attacks. He can re-roll failed Willpower tests to resist any psychic powers that affect his mind. This talent does not affect psychic powers that have a physical effect, such as Smite or Assail.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Resistance (Psychic Powers), Willpower 30","aptitudes":"Willpower, Defence","benefit":"May reroll failed WP tests to resist psychic powers.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"Ls0LWRBnOPzcxEKq"}
{"name":"Daemonologist","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is practiced in the dark arts, and knowledgeable in the strengths and vulnerabilities of Warp creatures. He is especially skilled at banishing Daemons&mdash;or harnessing them&mdash;through the use of his psychic abilities.</p>\n<p>Effect: When the character takes the Focus Power action and the target of the psychic power is a Daemon, he gains a +10 bonus to the Focus Power test. At the GM&rsquo;s discretion, this bonus may apply to other tests, such as rituals to summon or bind a Daemon.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Psy rating 3, Willpower 45, Forbidden Lore (Daemonology)","aptitudes":"Psyker, Willpower","benefit":"fokus boni against Daemons","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"M0BXBlgEoj0ICK3n"}
{"name":"Marksman","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s steady hand and eagle eye allow him to keep crosshairs steady on any target, regardless of range. Distance is no protection against the character&rsquo;s marksmanship, and he suffers no penalties for making Ballistic Skill tests at Long or Extreme range.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 35","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Finesse","benefit":"No penalties for firing at long or extreme range.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"O2drdttuFn5lFDCB"}
{"name":"Hotshot Pilot","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>When the situation calls for it, the opeator stretches the bounds of his abilities, displaying impressive feats of manoeuvring. This experience has also taught the Acolyte how to recover from what might become fatal mishaps for a less skilled operator attempting such manoeuvres. When the Acolyte succeeds on an Operate test (or Survival test in the case of a living steed), he may voluntarily suffer 1 level of Fatigue to add a number of degrees of success equal to half of his Agility bonus. When the Acolyte fails an Operate test (or Survival test in the case of a living steed), he may voluntarily suffer 1 level of Fatigue in order to reduce the degrees of failure by an amount equal to his Agility bonus, to a minimum of 1.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 2 in Survival or any Operate skill, Agility 35","aptitudes":"Agility, Tech","benefit":"Fatigue for DOS in operate/survival rolls","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"P66VgyZdMWdddtUl"}
{"name":"Mechadendrite Use*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Weapon, Utility</p>\n<p>The Acolyte is trained in the use of a particular kind of mechadendrite (see page 183) in much the same way as Weapon Training allows the use of weapons. Though there are many different types of mechadendrites, this talent divides them into two broad categories:</p>\n<p>&bull; Weapon: Mechadendrites of this type end in either ranged or close combat weapons, and have the supplemental power supplies and mechanical support necessary for combat.</p>\n<p>&bull; Utility: Including such varied types as Manipulator, Medicae, Utility, Optical, and countless others, these generally require less hardy mountings, but all function in a similar manner.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Mechanicus Implants","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Tech","benefit":"Gain ability to use certain Mechadendrites","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"PwFbdUBSom72DzBu"}
{"name":"Grenadier","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte knows that grenades and other explosives are amongst the most effective ways to bring down marauding alien beasts, or to quickly thin out hordes of lesser xenos monstrosities. When the character misses with a thrown weapon or weapon with the Blast quality, he may reduce the distance it scatters by a number of metres up to half his BS bonus.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 35","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Finesse","benefit":"reduce the scatter distance of missed throw/blast rolls","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"QkDGTNNJlE7MkahT"}
{"name":"One-on-One","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is a master of single combat. Without the distractions of multiple opponents, he fights at his best, taking every opening and leaving none.</p>\n<p>Effect: When fighting a single enemy in melee combat, the character scores extra degrees of success on successful Weapon Skill tests equal to half of his Weapon Skill bonus (rounded down).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 40","aptitudes":"Finesse, Weapon Skill","benefit":"extra DOS in One on One Meele","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"S6wD7p313T7enrYH"}
{"name":"Swift Attack","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s ability with weapons is legendary, allowing him to attack with amazing speed in melee. He can make the Swift Attack action (see page 225).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 30","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Finesse","benefit":"May make multiple melee attacks.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"S7qqK0eUKvt2bqES"}
{"name":"Quick Draw","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has practised so frequently with his weapons that they practically leap into his hands in response to a simple thought. As a Free Action, the character may draw and ready a Pistol or Basic weapon, or a one-handed Melee weapon.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Agility, Finesse","benefit":"Draw weapon as Free Action.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"SWFJ4tQ1BhckDhgP"}
{"name":"Daemonhunter","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Through years of experience and countless encounters that would blast the sanity and soul of a lesser man, the Acolyte has honed his abilities to uncover and destroy the Daemon wherever it may be found. He knows and recognises the spoor of the Daemon, and his righteous anger ensures that his blows land squarely on the unholy adversary.</p>\n<p>Effect: The Acolyte may re-roll failed Awareness and Psyniscience tests to detect the presence of Daemons. In addition, his attacks against Daemons gain the Proven (3) quality.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Forbidden Lore (Daemonology), Willpower 40","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Tech","benefit":"re-roll failed Awareness and Psyniscience tests","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"TebdjhM7rp2Nv6ry"}
{"name":"Sound Constitution","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte gains an additional wound. He can purchase this talent additional times up to twice his Toughness bonus. When he gains this talent multiple times, note the number of times it has been taken after the talent, such as Sound Constitution (3).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Toughness, General","benefit":"Gain an additional wound.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"UUJX0Q8vEKLIGofF"}
{"name":"Catfall","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Gymnastic ability and natural balance enables the Acolyte to fall great distances without harm. He automatically reduces the effective distance of all falls by a number of metres equal to his Agility bonus, ignoring this distance as if it did not exist. He also adds +20 to his Acrobatics skill tests when using the Jump special skill use, as it pertains to reducing damage from falling.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 30","aptitudes":"Agility, Fieldcraft","benefit":"Reduce falling damage.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"UXEz9UjPCyDefjs1"}
{"name":"Purity of Hatred*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Specialisations: Any group for which the character possesses</p>\n<p>the Hatred talent</p>\n<p>The Acolyte has honed his hatred to a razor&rsquo;s edge, pure and unsullied by mercy or doubt. When facing the object of his hatred, whether it be the witch, mutant, heretic, or traitor, the Acolyte is an instrument of the Emperor&rsquo;s Will, despatching His judgement upon the enemies of humanity as if guided by His very hand. When selecting this talent, the character chooses one specific group for which he possesses the Hatred talent. Against opponents of this group, the Acolyte&rsquo;s attacks gain the Vengeful (9) quality. If the Acolyte&rsquo;s weapon or attacks already possess this quality, decrease the value by one (to a minimum of 1).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Hatred (Any)","aptitudes":"Ofence, Willpower","benefit":"gain Vengeful against an enemy of hatred","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"Uoo7bMQfhxgwBe0u"}
{"name":"Enemy*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Any listed in the sidebar The Powers of Askellon above, and others at GM&rsquo;s discretion</p>\n<p>The opposite of Peer (see page 130); the Acolyte is particularly despised and possibly hunted by a specific social group or organisation, heretical cult, or xenos race. He suffers an additional &ndash;10 penalty to Fellowship and Influence tests when dealing with this group, and the GM can use them to complicate his life from time to time. Unlike other talents, Enemy does not cost any xp to purchase and cannot be taken as an advance. Instead the GM and player can agree to award it when appropriate to the adventure or campaign. It can be removed with the approval of the GM, if the character has redeemed himself with the group in question. The Enemy talent can be awarded multiple times for the same group, in which case it should be listed as Enemy (X), with X equalling the number of times the talent has been awarded. This can be used to represent groups who particularly hate the Acolyte and want to see him dead. In game terms, the penalty to Fellowship tests increases to &ndash;10 times X.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"General, Social","benefit":"An organization or group particularly despises  the character","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"V0Tbd4bBSEqQpjy4"}
{"name":"Technical Knock","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Either through the ease of long practice, or the proper ritual to appease a weapon&rsquo;s machine spirit, the Acolyte can clear stoppages with a simple knock or solid smack of his hand to a weapon. Once per round, he may attempt to unjam a gun (see page 224) as a Half Action rather than a Full Action. He must touch the weapon to make use of this talent.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Intelligence 30","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Tech","benefit":"Un-jam gun as Half Action.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"VEybrI16xpUGAHhV"}
{"name":"Killing Strike","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>With expert precision, the Acolyte can land blows which defy his opponent&rsquo;s ability to counter, slicing through defences as surely as a powerblade cuts flesh. At the beginning of each of his turns, the character may spend a Fate point to make his melee attacks unavoidable with the Dodge and Parry skills until the end of the round. Other means of avoiding or stopping attacks (such as displacer fields or alien protective devices) are unaffected.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 50","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Offence","benefit":"Spend Fate point to make melee attacks unavoidable","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"WM9DAqic6ismK5KR"}
{"name":"Keen Intuition","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has trained extensively to notice objects that seem out of place or hidden. This can bring the smallest irregularity to prominence, revealing the heresy festering beneath the surface. After failing an Awareness skill test, the character can re-roll the test with a &ndash;10 modifier.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Intelligence 35","aptitudes":"Perception, Social","benefit":"Can retry Awareness test once with â€“10 modifier.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"WlEsVqNnBWelFNU6"}
{"name":"Independent Targetin","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has developed his situational awareness to a point where he can fire in two directions within a split second. When firing two weapons as part of a single action (using the Two-Weapon Fighting talent, for example), the character does not need his targets to be within 10 metres of each other.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 40","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Finesse","benefit":"Fire at multiple targets more than 10 metres apart","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"XJnBMFCsmeLhSqaw"}
{"name":"Field Vivisection*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Specialisations: Ranged, Melee</p>\n<p>The Acolyte is well-versed in the blasphemous anatomy of his xenos foes, and uses this knowledge to utmost effect, both in the laboratorium and on the battlefield. Each time this talent is taken, the character selects the Specialisation that matches the Characteristic and Aptitude pair (Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill) used in purchase. When using the Called Shot action with a melee or ranged attack (depending on the Specialisation) against a target for which the character has the appropriate Forbidden Lore (Xenos) skill, he makes a Medicae (WS) or Medicae (BS) test in place of the normal Weapon Skill or Ballistic Skill test.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill 40, Forbidden Lore (Xenosâ€“Any), Rank 2 in the Medicae skill","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill, Knowledge","benefit":"Know the anatomy of your xenos foes","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"XOZWVxa1bfM6Km8u"}
{"name":"Weapon Training*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Bolt, Chain, Flame, Heavy, Las, Launcher, Melta, Plasma, Power, Low-Tech, Shock, and Solid Projectile</p>\n<p>The Acolyte can use all weapons with Class: Pistol, Basic, Melee, Throwing, and Vehicle within the group he has selected with this talent. When a character attempts to use a weapon he does not have the correct Weapon Training talent for, he suffers a &ndash;20 penalty to any relevant Weapon Skill or Ballistic Skill test.</p>\n<p>The character can only use weapons with Class: Heavy without suffering the &ndash;20 penalty if he has both Weapon Training in the appropriate group and Weapon Training (Heavy). This talent can be taken more than once, each time with a different Specialisation. Note that a character without the Weapon Training (Low-Tech) talent operating a weapon that functions as a Low-Tech weapon in certain circumstances does not suffer this penalty, so long as he has the applicable Weapon Training talent for the weapon (Power for a power sword, for example).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"General, Finesse","benefit":"Use Weapon Group without penalty","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"Y3HKj6ahp0P6rvS7"}
{"name":"Leaping Dodge","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has become practiced at escaping weapons that cover an area to deadly effect, from flamers to strange xenos devices. When he would make an Agility test to avoid attacks from weapons with the Spray quality, he may make the test using his Dodge (Ag) skill instead.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 35, Rank 2 in the Dodge skill","aptitudes":"Agility, Defence","benefit":"Use dodge instead of Ag to avoid spray","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"YJcjknFJQUTbNcMc"}
{"name":"Jaded","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s wide travels have shown him both wonders and horrors beyond the ken of most. The galaxy has thrown its worst at him and he has yet to flinch. Mundane events, from death&rsquo;s horrific visage to xenos abominations, do not force him to gain Insanity points or make Fear tests. Daemons, Warp manifestations, and other unnatural effects still affect him normally.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 40","aptitudes":"Willpower, Defence","benefit":"Ignore mundane horrors.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"YLWsediTc97e2hEJ"}
{"name":"Exotic Weapon Training*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Each different exotic weapon</p>\n<p>The Acolyte is trained to use a particularly obscure type of weapon, such as a graviton gun or needle pistol. Weapons requiring this unique talent are noted in their armoury descriptions. Unlike other kinds of weapons training, this talent applies only to a single weapon type and not a class of weapons. Note that an Exotic weapon with the Heavy class would also require the Weapon Training (Heavy) talent as well as Exotic Weapon Training in that specific weapon.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Finesse","benefit":"Gain proficiency with one exotic weapon type.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"Yuh4gMADUBj8gObv"}
{"name":"Rapid Reload","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The firing ranges and weapon drill chambers are the Acolyte&rsquo;s constant abode. Hours of reloading countless magazines or power cells means that he can replace them without looking and without thinking, even in the middle of combat. He halves all reload times, rounding down. Thus, a Half Action reload becomes a Free Action, a Full Action reload becomes a Half Action, and so on.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Agility, Fieldcraft","benefit":"Reduce reload time.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"av3L5koYPCpugzgv"}
{"name":"Weapon-Tech","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte calls upon the blessings of the Omnissiah, channelling his faith into his weapon and performing armament rituals to more readily smite his foes. Once per combat encounter, as a Free Action, this character may enhance any Melta, Plasma, Power, or Exotic weapon he is personally wielding. This increases the weapon&rsquo;s damage and penetration by an amount equal to the character&rsquo;s Intelligence bonus until the end of the round.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Intelligence 40, Tech Use +10","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Tech","benefit":"Increase potency of advanced weaponry.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"b2Fbzdcle5CugYjq"}
{"name":"Ambassador Imperialis","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Whether from serving in the fleet of a Rogue Trader or dealing with xenos mercenaries on frontier worlds, the Acolyte is experienced in dealing with alien and the most divergent of non-Imperial cultures, able to avoid the subtle faux pas that can so easily cause a negotiation to deteriorate into bloodshed. The character reduces any penalty to Interaction skill tests for dealing with xenos or non-Imperial NPCs by 20. In addition, once per encounter, he can reroll a failed Interaction skill test when interacting with such an NPC.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Fellowship 35, Intelligence 35","aptitudes":"Perception, Social","benefit":"reduces any penalty to Interaction skill tests for dealing with xenos or non-Imperial NPCs by 20.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"bHAnUiqt5yD8jP28"}
{"name":"Ambidextrous","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>This talent does not represent true ambidexterity so much as sufficient training with both hands to make the distinction moot. When combined with Two-Weapon Wielder talent, the penalty for making attacks with both weapons in the same turn drops to &ndash;10.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ag 30","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Balistic Skill","benefit":"Reduce penalties for using two weapons.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"csBN69GwpNwZceWB"}
{"name":"Blinding Fight","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Years of practice and development of his other senses allows the Acolyte to fight in close combat without the benefit of sight. He ignores all penalties for fighting with a melee weapon while suffering from obscured vision, permitting him to fight in fog, smoke, or darkness more effectively. See page 229 for a full list of normal penalties based on lighting and vision. Note this talent only improves his chances to hit with melee weapons, and has no effect on ranged weapon attacks.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Perception 30","aptitudes":"Perception, Fieldcraft","benefit":"Eliminates melee combat penalties for obscured vision.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"dSCBtIkqEHxMorke"}
{"name":"Hardened Soul","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte knows that he must sacrifice his own salvation in order to safeguard humanity, but that he must resist the corruption for as long as possible. Through practiced meditation, self-flagellation, prayer and fasting, force of will, or even sorcerous rites, the character staves off the effects of his growing corruption, delaying the inevitable.</p>\n<p>Effect: Whenever the character would gain Corruption points, he may reduce the amount gained by half (rounded up) and gain Insanity points equal to the amount reduced.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 35, 10 Corruption points","aptitudes":"Defence, Willpower","benefit":"gain insanity instead of corruption","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"eHxuTrUs9cazSKsx"}
{"name":"Skilled Rider","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Often, the best way to overcome the heretic is with merciless speed, and so many Acolytes make extensive use of vehicles and mounts in their pursuit of humanity&rsquo;s enemies. Whether the character has used his prized bike until it feels like an extension of his own body, or he has the experience necessary to instantly adjust to the strange mounts and vehicles found across the Askellon Sector, moving to or from the saddle or pilot&rsquo;s seat is second nature. Whenever the character would be thrown from or tossed about within his vehicle, he makes an Ordinary (+10) Agility test. If he succeeds, the character may choose to either land safely on his feet or retain in his original position in the vehicle. In addition, once per round the character can attempt an Ordinary (+10) Agility test to Mount or Dismount a vehicle as a Free Action.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 2 in any Operate skill","aptitudes":"Agility, Fieldcraft","benefit":"You know what you are riding and its hard to throw you off","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"eeIfUez5zLEc3hxy"}
{"name":"Bulwark of Faith","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s faith is both a shield and a weapon. So filled with righteous fervour is he that Daemons recoil from the blinding light of his faith, their unholy forms sundered.</p>\n<p>Effect: When the character passes a Fear test caused by a Daemon, the Daemon suffers 1 Energy damage ignoring armour and Toughness bonus for each degree of success on the Fear test.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 45, Iron Faith","aptitudes":"Defence, Willpower","benefit":"passed fear test causes Deamons damage","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"fM9cMTxruVZkUzbD"}
{"name":"Inspiring Aura","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s strength of will inspires those under his command and his comrades in equal measure. Looking to his faithful example, his allies can overcome their own fear in order to do the Emperor&rsquo;s work.</p>\n<p>Effect: The character can affect allies of any kind&mdash;not only subordinates&mdash;with the Terrify special use for the Command skill (see page 101 of the Dark Heresy Core Rulebook). This need not represent threats and intimidation, but might represent inspiring words, encouragement, or sheer steadfastness in the face of terrifying foes.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Halo of Command","aptitudes":"Leadership, Willpower","benefit":"effect all allies with the command skill","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"i6R8GuBhXdKr8A1i"}
{"name":"Deny the Witch","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte draws on his faith and mental fortitude to act as his shield against those tainted by the Warp. The character may use his Willpower characteristic when making an Evasion Reaction against ranged or melee attacks against him made with psychic powers. When successfully evading an attack with an area of effect, the character does not move but instead is simply unaffected by the psychic power.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 35","aptitudes":"Willpower, Defence","benefit":"Can use Willpower to Evade against psychic attacks.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"iEoPRSzou2uwuHsa"}
{"name":"Leap Up","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>A combination of athletic ability and speed allows the Acolyte to spring to his feet in virtually any circumstance. He can stand up as a Free Action.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 30","aptitudes":"Agility, General","benefit":"Stand as a Free Action.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"iIPsQPhjmRFvFudh"}
{"name":"Hatred*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Chaos Space Marines, Daemons, Mutants, Psykers, Xenos (specific), others including groups from the sidebar The Powers of Askellon on page 94.</p>\n<p>A group, organisation, or race has wronged the character in the past, fuelling this animosity. When fighting opponents of that group in close combat, the Acolyte gains a +10 bonus to all Weapon Skill tests made against them. He also finds it difficult to back down from a fight with his hated foe, and must make a Challenging (+0) Willpower test to retreat or surrender when fighting them, unless suicidally outnumbered or outclassed.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Social","benefit":"Gain +10 bonus to attack hated creatures.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"iKG0CqQfb1QYRAXA"}
{"name":"Whirlwind of Deat","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>When facing massed opponents in close quarters, the Acolyte becomes a streak of blows, moving, hacking, gutting, and beheading his enemies with ceaseless fury. As a Half Action, the character may make one Standard Attack action (see page 224) with a melee weapon against a foe, plus one additional Standard Attack action with the same weapon targeting each other foe also engaged in melee combat with the character beyond the first (to a maximum number of attacks up to his Weapon Skill bonus).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 40","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Finesse","benefit":"Make one attack for each melee opponent.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"iNMWRPd4FIXwiUHy"}
{"name":"Penitent Psyker","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Psykers are hated and shunned throughout the Imperium, and even those psykers who serve the Emperor often struggle with their curse. Whether a rogue psyker taken under an Inquisitor&rsquo;s wing or a sanctioned psyker whose faith condemns his abilities, such an individual might develop the ability to act as a kind of psychic lightning rod, sacrificing his own lesh in order to protect his allies from the Warp-spawned powers of the witch and wyrd.&nbsp; When the psyker or an ally within 10 metres becomes the target of a psychic power, the psyker may voluntarily sufer any number of levels of Fatigue. Each level of Fatigue sufered grants the target a +10 bonus on any Opposed test to resist the power or Evasion test to avoid its efects. If the target&rsquo;s test to resist or avoid the power results in a roll of doubles, the psyker generates Psychic Phenomena, just as if he had used the Focus Power action.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Psy rating, Strong Minded, Willpower 40","aptitudes":"Psyker, Defence","benefit":"Protect an ally from psychic attacks","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"ir0RgZkN2RZG91ii"}
{"name":"Iron Resolve","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is inured to the terrors of both combat and the</p>\n<p>Warp, knowing that he must control his fear in order to face foes that threaten both body and soul. When confronted with the machinations of heretics, threats to life and limb, and even the otherworldly creatures of the Warp, the Acolyte stands firm.</p>\n<p>Effect: After failing a Fear or Pinning test, the character can re-roll the test with a &ndash;10 modifier.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Intelligence 35, Tech-Use, Trade (Armourer)","aptitudes":"Defence, Willpower","benefit":"re-roll failed fear/pinning test","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"jEV1G5D62ReZ7Pwb"}
{"name":"Luminen Shock","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The energies charged in the Acolyte&rsquo;s Luminen Capacitors can be expelled by touching a foe. The character always counts as being equipped with a melee weapon that inflicts 1d10 plus his WPB in Energy damage, with Pen 0 and the Shocking quality. He always counts as having Weapon Training for it and after making this attack, he must pass a Toughness test or suffer 1 level of Fatigue.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Luminen Capacitors, Mechanicus Implants","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Tech","benefit":"Character can discharge energy in melee attack.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"jHe1n1xAidHdD624"}
{"name":"Clues from  the Crowds","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>It is often difficult to extract information from groups such as hive gangs or Administratum scribes, as often numbers can bolster recalcitrance to questioning. A veteran Acolyte knows that such groups can hold critical information to complete an investigation, and can throw more effective nets when interrogating groups and reveal valued clues. Once per day, he can re-roll a test made to gather information from a group of people.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Fellowship 30","aptitudes":"General, Social","benefit":"Can re-roll a test made to gather information from  a group.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"k5VhP50U1Tpb004l"}
{"name":"Precision Killer*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Ranged, Melee</p>\n<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s eye, hand, and weapon act seamlessly together, placing his attacks exactly where he intends. When this talent is taken, the character selects the Specialisation that matches the Characteristic and Aptitude pair (Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill) used in purchase. When making a Called Shot (see page 219) with a melee or ranged attack (depending on the Specialisation), he does not suffer the usual &ndash;20 penalty.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 40 or Weapon Skill 40","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill, Finesse","benefit":"No penalty to making Called Shot in either Ranged  or Melee Combat.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"kmkobZtcaKyuiyxF"}
{"name":"Warp Sense","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s senses have evolved to perceive the Warp in parallel with the physical world. The character can use the Psyniscience Skill as a Free Action instead of as a Half Action. He can also passively detect psychic effects and entities without the need to actively seek them out. Whenever the character could detect such a Warp signature or a creature, the GM can allow him to make a Psyniscience skill test to detect it, in the same way he could use Awareness to spot an ambush without knowing it is there.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Perception 30, Psy rating, Psyniscience","aptitudes":"Perception, Psyker","benefit":"Allows Psyniscience test as Free Action.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"kzDleedT1kfXwQrg"}
{"name":"Resistance*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Cold, Fear, Heat, Poisons, Psychic Powers,</p>\n<p>Radiation, Vacuum, Other</p>\n<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s background, experience, training, exposure, or plain stubbornness has developed a resistance within him. Each time he selects this talent, choose one area of resistance. He gains a +10 bonus when making tests to resist effects of this type. The GM can require approval for certain choices, or justification based on the Acolyte&rsquo;s past.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Toughness, Defence","benefit":"Gain +10 bonus to particular resistance test.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"lqX6kuz3af9J3cQM"}
{"name":"Warp Conduit","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The sheer power of the Acolyte&rsquo;s mind allows him to channel vast amounts of Warp energy when he chooses. When Pushing (see page 194), before rolling his Focus Power test the character may spend one Fate Point to add an additional 1d5 to the effective psy rating of the power. Channelling such vast amounts of power is dangerous, however, and so he adds +30 to rolls on Table 6&ndash;2: Psychic Phenomena when he makes as a result of this talent.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Spend Fate point to add 1d5 to psy rating.","aptitudes":"Psy rating, Strong Minded, Willpower 50","benefit":"Willpower, Psyker","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"pGTXpmsKCu9Y67yf"}
{"name":"Double Tap","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is practiced in making dual attacks, and can almost subconsciously tell when his hits strike to best effect. When making a second ranged attack action in the same turn against the same target, he gains a +20 bonus to the attack test if his first attack scored one or more successful hits.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Two-Weapon Wielder","aptitudes":"Finesse, Offence","benefit":"Successful first attack grants bonus to second attack.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"pUjDSDrFV0XdgEKI"}
{"name":"Ferric Summons","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has trained himself in better use of his Ferric Lure Implants (see page 182). He can summon to his hand an unsecured metal object weighing up to 2 kilograms per point of his Willpower bonus, and can summon such objects up to 40 metres distant.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ferric Lure Implants, Mechanicus Implants","aptitudes":"Willpower, Tech","benefit":"Can summon larger metallic objects.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"ptLEWV4s9PjOFaMW"}
{"name":"Takedown","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>When making a Standard Attack or Charge action, the Acolyte can declare that he is attempting a takedown his target. He then rolls to hit (using his Weapon Skill) as normal, applying all the regular modifiers for the attack action. If the character hits and would have done at least 1 point of damage (after reduction for Armour and Toughness), no wounds are caused. Instead, the opponent must make a Challenging (+0) Toughness test or be Stunned for 1 Round and knocked Prone. In addition, when performing a Stun Action, the character does not suffer the normal &ndash;20 penalty to his Weapon Skill.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Offence","benefit":"Make special attack to stun opponent.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"qSxfeFHBJkLXnWJd"}
{"name":"Nowhere to Hid","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s keen eye ensures he can spot soft points even in the most impregnable of protective cover. When he damages cover (see page 229), the character adds his degrees of success from the attack to the reduction of the cover&rsquo;s Armour value. If using a weapon that does not require a skill test, he adds 1 instead.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Perception 30","aptitudes":"Perception, Offence","benefit":"Can add DoS from the attack to reduce armour value  of cover.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"qZ68B9b7awafdtqS"}
{"name":"Lexographer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>From years poring over dusty tomes and examining ancient ruins on forgotten worlds&mdash;and perhaps even speaking face-toface with inhuman beings&mdash;the Acolyte has become an expert in deciphering lost human languages as well as those of xenos. The character can attempt any Linguistics skill in which he is not trained as an untrained skill test as if it were not a Specialist skill.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 3 in Linguistics (Any)","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Knowledge","benefit":"The character can attempt any Linguistics skill as untrained","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"rbbGVQl5BYD3DQ1Y"}
{"name":"Face in a Crowd","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>A successful investigation often involves trailing suspects without their knowledge, the better to follow them to hidden dens of heretical worship or criminal activity. With training, the Acolyte can ensure none notice his presence, through careful replication of a crowd&rsquo;s mannerisms or even joining gatherings while still keeping a careful eye on his quarry. When employing the Shadowing special use of the Stealth skill, he can use his Fellowship characteristic instead of his Agility.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Clues from the Crowds, Fellowship 35","aptitudes":"Fellowship, Social","benefit":"Can use Fellowship instead of Agility when Shadowing","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"roSjh6R1CqnCtcPJ"}
{"name":"Inescapable Attack*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte can anticipate his opponent&rsquo;s reactions, and ensures his hits strike no matter how a foe tries to avoid them. This talent applies to Melee or Ranged attacks, depending on the Speciality chosen. After making a successful attack test of the appropriate type as part of an All Out Attack, Called Shot, Charge, Standard Attack, or Stun action, the character imposes a penalty on all evasion attempts (Dodge or Parry tests) made against this attack equal to 10 times the total degrees of success scored on the attack test.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 40 or Weapon Skill 40, Perception 35","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill, Finesse","benefit":"Attacker imposes penalty on DoS from Evasion test equal to DoS his initial attack.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"tflG7YodM4iQ4t6n"}
{"name":"Bodyguard","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has trained to protect his allies or superiors, prepared to even throw himself in the way of a bolt shell or whirring chain blade if necessary.</p>\n<p>Effect: After an enemy makes a successful attack against an ally, the character may use a Reaction to move up to his Half Move distance in order to interpose himself between the attacker and target. The attack is then resolved against the character instead of the original target. In the case of a melee attack, the character may also attempt to Parry the attack as part of his Reaction.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 35","aptitudes":"Agility, Defence","benefit":"Take a hit for an ally","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"tgxzgfK7p8E0ckPp"}
{"name":"Flagellant","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte knows that pain is cleansing, and regularly mortifies his own flesh to atone for his sins. As a Full Action, the character can inlict some suitable punishment on his own body, sufering 1d5&ndash;2 levels of Fatigue (to a minimum of 1). He then gains a +10 bonus on Willpower tests to resist Fear, Pinning, psychic powers, or sufering Corruption, for one hour or until the end of the current encounter. If the Acolyte also possesses the Frenzy talent, he can enter a Frenzied state as a Free Action while under the effects of this talent.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 30","aptitudes":"Ofence, Toughness","benefit":"gain stat boni for fatigue","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"u1KqRIrCrbK1nt7X"}
{"name":"Xenosavant","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>In his study and prosecution of the xenos threat, the Acolyte has become well-versed in the ways and forms of the myriad alien races that menace humanity. The character can attempt any Forbidden Lore (Xenos) test in which he is not trained as an untrained skill test as if it were not a Specialist skill.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 3 in Forbidden Lore (Xenosâ€“Any)","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Knowledge","benefit":"roll any Forbidden Lore (Xenos) test as an untrained skill test","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"u5lgOMCQjLzlfLAQ"}
{"name":"Devastating Assau","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte launches a furious attack on his foe, the rage of the Emperor powering his assault. Once per turn, after resolving an All Out Attack action that successfully hits, the character may make a second All Out Attack action against the same target as a Free Action, with the same bonuses and penalties as the first.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 35","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Offence","benefit":"A successful All Out Attack grants a second attack.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"wyJs0Z4jxhmbDxAH"}
{"name":"Coordinated Interrogation","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>A trained Acolyte, especially when working in conjunction with fellow veteran Acolytes, can induce cooperation from even the most hardened of suspects and captured heretics. He gains a +10 bonus to all Interrogation tests, and gains an additional +5 for each other character participating in the interrogation who also has Coordinated Interrogation. This counts as test assistance, and thus also gains the standard assistance bonuses as per page 25.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Clues from the Crowds, Strength 40 or Willpower 40","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Social","benefit":"+10 bonus to all Interrogate tests, additional +5 for others who also have Coordinated Interrogation.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/2.png","effects":[],"_id":"xI022D2ogS1l7eVI"}
{"name":"Double Team","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has experience of fighting in paired teams that work together to take down their enemies. When Ganging Up on an opponent, he gains an additional +10 bonus to Weapon Skill tests. If both the characters that outnumber the enemy have this talent, then both gain an additional +10 bonus, for a total of +20. This bonus is in addition to the normal bonus gained from Ganging Up on an opponent (see page 229).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"General, Offence","benefit":"Gain additional +10 for outnumbering opponent.","tier":1,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/1.png","effects":[],"_id":"xNScsXlNclUrSDcL"}
{"name":"Adamantium Faith","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has become inured to horrors that would cripple lesser men. This might come from years of facing incoming fire, staring down the terrors of the Warp, or simply his absolute faith in the Emperor. He can subtract his Willpower bonus from his degrees of failure on a failed Fear or Pinning test. If this reduces the result to zero or less, he counts as having passed the Fear test with 1 degree of success.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Jaded, Resistance (Fear), Willpower 45","aptitudes":"Willpower, Defence","benefit":"Reduces DoF from failed Pinning and Fear tests.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"2QA1RzRlCoDnqXE9"}
{"name":"Aegis of Contempt","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Inquisitor wards his mind and soul to withstand the inluence of the Archenemy of Mankind. Just as his Acolytes help him to guard Mankind against such damnation, so does he guard them, strengthening their resolve with benedictions of hatred and cleansing prayers. <br />Whenever this character or an ally within 10 metres gains Corruption, reduce the amount gained by 1 to a minimum of 0. In addition, an ally within 10 metres can spend a Fate point to gain 0 Corruption instead. These efects do not stack when there are multiple characters with this talent within range.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Shared Destiny, Shield of Contempt, Hatred (any)","aptitudes":"Defence, Leadership","benefit":"reduce allies corruption taken","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"v3aEbAkZu7PdhfPc"}
{"name":"Assassin Strike","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The character&rsquo;s natural agility and graceful martial form turn him into a dervish of death in combat. After making a melee attack, a successful Challenging (+0) Acrobatics skill test allows the Acolyte to move at half rate as a Free Action. He may only make this move once per round, and the character&rsquo;s opponent does not receive a free attack resulting from this move.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Acrobatics, Agility 40","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Fieldcraft","benefit":"After melee attack, test Acrobatics to move.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"7HmaFrBBmqnCXEjW"}
{"name":"Bastion of Iron Will","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s sheer willpower and psychic focus have become one and the same, over years of practice and training, such that their combined use is second nature. He adds 5 x his psy rating to any Opposed test he makes when defending against psychic powers.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Psy rating, Strong Minded, Willpower 40","aptitudes":"Willpower, Psyker","benefit":"Gain bonus for Opposed tests against  psychic powers.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"w1pO7Fi5BntMEVZu"}
{"name":"Blademaster","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s mastery of bladed weapons and their martial disciplines has no peer. When attacking with any bladed weapon, including chainswords, axes, and power swords, he can re-roll one missed attack per round.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 30, Weapon Training (any melee)","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Finesse","benefit":"Reroll missed attack, once per round.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"1LupoLDxKCJ1BQ6C"}
{"name":"Crushing Blow","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has the ability to focus his entire body into close combat attacks. He adds half his Weapon Skill bonus (rounding up) to damage he inflicts with melee attacks.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 40","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Offence","benefit":"Add half WS bonus to damage inflicted in melee.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"k7uULaguYHS5nexd"}
{"name":"Daemonic Disruption","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Untouchable&rsquo;s very presence is anathema to Daemons, and only the strongest can threaten him. Creatures of the Warp that lay claw upon the Untouchable must struggle to maintain their hold in reality, lest mere contact hurl them back into the Immaterium.</p>\n<p>Effect: Whenever a creature with the Warp Instability trait makes a successful attack test against this character, it must immediately test for Warp Instability after resolving the attack.&nbsp;</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Bane of the Daemon, Willpower 50, Untouchable elite advance","aptitudes":"Willpower","benefit":"forces Warp Instability rolls","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"2tVSxhq1bkkkhj98"}
{"name":"Dark Soul","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Whether through devotion to the Emperor, sheer willpower, single-minded dedication to his duty, or the blessing of some dark power, the Acolyte&rsquo;s internal corruption remains outwardly invisible. With no mutations to mark him as accursed, the Acolyte can continue his radical work without detection.</p>\n<p>Effect: When the character would test to gain a mutation as a result of increasing Corruption, he may choose to automatically pass the test. If he does, he also gains a Malignancy and increases his Corruption total by 1d10.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Hardened Soul, 20 Corruption points","aptitudes":"Toughness, Willpower","benefit":"Mutation is not enough","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"sT71iFIJXvZzUgZv"}
{"name":"Deathdealer*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Ranged, Melee</p>\n<p>The Acolyte can place his hits where they inflict maximum harm, such as gaps or joints in armour. When this talent is taken, the character selects the Specialisation that matches the prerequisite used in purchase (Melee with Weapon Skill, Ranged with Ballistic Skill). When the character&rsquo;s attack in that combat type inflicts Critical damage, he adds his Perception bonus to the damage result.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 45 or Weapon Skill 45","aptitudes":"Perception, Finesse","benefit":"Add Per bonus to damage inflicted in combat.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"K5upt9PSrV3XYj0K"}
{"name":"Delicate Interrogation","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Questioning suspects and witnesses is always a necessary part of any investigation. Such sessions must remain secretive or obscured, however, lest others learn of the Inquisition&rsquo;s interest, and a variety of subterfuges, deceptions, and outright threats come into play to aid this effort. Whenever the Acolyte would decrease his warband&rsquo;s Subtlety due to an interrogation, the amount of Subtlety lost is reduced by 1d5. If this results in a negative number, the Acolyte&rsquo;s skilled efforts increase the warband&rsquo;s Subtlety by 1.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Coordinated Interrogation, Fellowship 50","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Finesse","benefit":"Reduce Subtlety loss by 1d5 when conducting  an investigation.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"LT8xo5AW7rIEJixU"}
{"name":"Divine Protection","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Those who hunt the witch and mutant often prefer to use cleansing fire to purify their unclean enemies. As if to further demonstrate the cleansing power of flame, some such blessed warriors even use flamers and similar weapons when their allies are in the line of fire, yet miraculously leave them unafected. If a supposed ally does succumb to the flames, surely that is only evidence of concealed heresy. When the Acolyte attacks using a weapon with the Spray quality, it only strikes enemies within the area of effect; the attack does not harm allies.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 45, Willpower 35","aptitudes":"Finesse","benefit":"Spray weapons do not harm allies","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"X0oM77NjKCvEDyFE"}
{"name":"Eye of Vengeanc","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte can focus his intent on where it is likely to do most damage to his enemy and then strike his foe down with a single shot. Before making a ranged Standard Attack action, he can spend a Fate point. If he does so, he adds the number of degrees of success scored on the attack test to both his damage and penetration for the hit.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 50","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Offence","benefit":"Spend 1 Fate point to increase damage and penetration.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"mfSQh9GSIC94tSRr"}
{"name":"Favoured by  the Warp","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Whenever this character rolls on Table 6&ndash;2: Psychic Phenomena (see page 196), so long as he does not receive the Perils of the Warp result, he may roll a second time and choose which result he receives.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 35","aptitudes":"Willpower, Psyker","benefit":"Roll twice for Psychic Phenomena and  choose result.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"bU55rEOH0C55gkcl"}
{"name":"Flash of Insight","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Despite steady application of logic and careful analysis, some conundrums remain insoluble, but inspiration could come from outside sources, such as reading patterns from wisps of lho smoke or even making direct appeals to the Emperor for guidance. An Acolyte who has trained his mind to process such lateral data can leap to conclusions that direct thinking cannot provide, and thus quash even the most hidden of heresies. When stuck in an investigation, he can spend one Fate point to reveal a single clue or lead to aid in the progression of his efforts.&nbsp;</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Contact Network, Coordinated Interrogation, Intelligence 40","aptitudes":"Perception, Knowledge","benefit":"Spend 1 Fate point to reveal a clue","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"feLLWSVk1oyM7KTz"}
{"name":"Halo of Command","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has trained himself to better to lead and sway others, either motivating or terrifying those around him to greater levels. When targeting friendly NPCs through skills that have either the Social or Leadership Aptitudes (such as Charm, Command, and Intimidate), he can affect those within 100 times his Fellowship bonus in metres rather than 10 times that number.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Fellowship 40, Willpower 40","aptitudes":"Fellowship, Leadership","benefit":"Affect NPCs within 100xFelB metres with  Social skills.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"SwxzbOITF9oYukBx"}
{"name":"Hammer Blow","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte strikes a single blow with such focus and force that it breaks armour and pulps flesh as it strikes. When he uses an All Out Attack action to make a single melee attack, he can add half his Strength bonus (rounded up) to the weapon&rsquo;s penetration. The attack also counts as having the Concussive (2) weapon quality, to represent the shocking force of the blow&rsquo;s impact.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Crushing Blow","aptitudes":"Strength, Offence","benefit":"Make a thunderous strike with a melee weapon.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"bgbo8G333UANme7W"}
{"name":"Indomitable Conviction","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>An Inquisitor must often share a part of his burden of knowledge and understanding with those who serve alongside him. Although some Acolytes might succumb to madness and despair, those who undergo such mental trials with their sanity intact come out stronger for it. An Inquisitor can also beneit from such an experience, drawing strength from his comrades and renewing his faith in his duty to Mankind. Whenever this character or an ally within 10 metres gains Insanity, reduce the amount gained by 1. In addition, an ally within 10 metres can spend a Fate point to gain 0 Insanity instead. These efects do not stack when there are multiple characters with this talent within range.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Shared Destiny, Strength through Conviction, Resistance (Fear), Jaded","aptitudes":"Willpower, Defence","benefit":"Reduce insanity gained","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"EBQ4SowNiGkKlPOS"}
{"name":"Infused Knowledge","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has been imbued with a great breadth of lore, either through punishing noetic techniques or by arcane methods kept secret by the guardians of technology and learning. He counts as having all Common Lore and Scholastic Lore skills at rank 1 (Known)&mdash;basically, he knows something about everything. If he wishes to later improve his Lore skills, these advances must be bought using experience points (from rank 1) as normal. He also adds one degree of success to any successful Common or Scholastic Lore tests, due to his ingrained training.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Intelligence 40, Lore (any one)","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Knowledge","benefit":"Know a little bit about everything.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"nhRpo5zY7rIvAKzp"}
{"name":"Instrument of His Will","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte strikes down daemonic foes with holy fury, his blows landing as if guided by the hand of the Emperor Himself. The keen edge of his faith and hatred presents the true threat to the Daemon, not his physical strength or the potency of his weapon.</p>\n<p>Effect: After making a successful attack against a Daemon (this can include striking it with a psychic power), the character may spend a Fate point to increase the damage of the first hit he inflicts as part of that attack by an amount equal to twice his Willpower bonus. This additional damage ignores armour and Toughness bonus.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 50","aptitudes":"Offence, Willpower","benefit":"Fate point for additional dmg against demons","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"4xEblZfvXws1lyZv"}
{"name":"Into the Jaws of Hell","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Inquisitor&rsquo;s strength of conviction and faith in the Emperor&mdash; or perhaps the fear of his retribution&mdash;inspire those at his side to fight on, even in the face of overwhelming odds and the terrors of the galaxy. Servants and allies within 10 metres can subtract the Inquisitor&rsquo;s Fellowship bonus from their degrees of failure on a failed Fear or Pinning test, so long as the Inquisitor passes the test. If this reduces the degrees of failure to 0 or less, a character counts as having passed the test with 1 degree of success. The efects of this talent apply to Acolytes in the Inquisitor&rsquo;s warband and to other servants of the Imperium fighting under the Inquisitor&rsquo;s orders, as well as others at the GM&rsquo;s discretion.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Adamantium Faith, Halo of Command, Will of the Inquisitor","aptitudes":"Leadership, Willpower","benefit":"The Inquisitor inspires those who follow him, to resist fear","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"apcJtbEMTQfk2WfG"}
{"name":"Iron Faith","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s faith is as unyielding as plasteel, and it protects him against the unnatural aura of the daemonic. With the strength of his conviction, he faces down the otherworldly terrors of the Warp the way a lesser man might look down the barrel of a lasgun.</p>\n<p>Effect: The character is immune to the effects of the Baneful Presence trait.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Iron Resolve","aptitudes":"Defence, Willpower","benefit":"immune to the effects of the Baneful  Presence","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"NEuVgVj0NXogpGKc"}
{"name":"Lightning Attac","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s speed with weapons is unmatched, allowing him to launch flurries of attacks in melee. He can make the Lightning Attack action (see page 222).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Swift Attack","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Finesse","benefit":"Character may make many melee attacks with single roll.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"2oMwAMV1MmeBhrSt"}
{"name":"Luminen Blast","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The energies charged in the Acolyte&rsquo;s Luminen Capacitors can be expelled in a ranged attack. The character always counts as being equipped with a Pistol weapon with a 10m range. This can only be used in single shot mode, and deals 1d10 plus twice his Willpower bonus in Energy damage, with Pen 0 and the Shocking quality. The character always counts as having Weapon Training for this weapon and after making an attack with it, he must pass a Toughness test or suffer 1 level of Fatigue.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Luminen Shock, Luminen Capacitors, Mechanicus Implants","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Tech","benefit":"May discharge stored energy as a ranged attack.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"ILTOk518xERgTSPZ"}
{"name":"Mastery*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Any skill</p>\n<p>The Acolyte has mastered a single skill. He can spend a Fate point to automatically pass a skill test with his chosen skill, provided the final modifier to his skill test is Challenging (+0) or better. He scores a number of degrees of success equal to the characteristic bonus of the skill&rsquo;s associated characteristic. This talent may be taken more than once, each time for a different skill.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 4 in selected skill","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Knowledge","benefit":"May spend Fate point to succeed on test.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"s2UuZCf6np0YYccl"}
{"name":"Mighty Shot","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte knows the weak points in every type of armour and material, and has the skill to ensure that his shots land exactly where they can do the most damage. He adds half his Ballistic Skill bonus (rounded up) to damage he inflicts with ranged weapons.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 40","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Offence","benefit":"Add half BS bonus to ranged damage rolls.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"hjlTCLCOjAtYefg1"}
{"name":"Never Die","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s will or devotion to the Emperor can sustain him when his mortal body fails. He may spend one Fate point to ignore the effects of injury (such as those from Critical damage), Fatigue, and Stunning for a single combat, so long as they would not kill him immediately. This talent does not prevent the damage, but allows him to temporarily ignore its effects for the duration of the combat. Once the encounter ends, the effects trigger as normal.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 50, Toughness 50","aptitudes":"Toughness, Defence","benefit":"Ignore penalties from Critical damage by  spending Fate point.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"qs2F6CikTKPOiitO"}
{"name":"Preternatural Speed","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is a swift-moving bringer of death, a living, bloody scythe before whom foes die like corn before the reaper. When making a Charge action, he doubles his normal Charge movement (for instance, if he has an Agility bonus of 3 and thus a Charge movement of 9 metres, his movement is then doubled to 18 metres with this talent).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 40, Agility 50","aptitudes":"Agility, Offence","benefit":"Double speed when charging.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"abWgPhfeU7yhumNN"}
{"name":"Sanctic Purity","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Sanctic Daemonology is often considered the most pure of psychic disciplines. Practitioners can seem beyond the dangers of the Warp that all too often plague other psykers. Such mastery is taxing, but an experienced Daemonologist can resist the influence of the Warp where other psykers would succumb.</p>\n<p>Effect: When the character triggers Psychic Phenomena when manifesting a power from the Sanctic Daemonology discipline, he may spend a Fate point in order to negate the result entirely.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Daemonologist, Favoured by the Warp, Willpower 50","aptitudes":"Psyker, Willpower","benefit":"spent a fate point do negate a special Psychic Phenomena event","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"85QS7K8j8w0HP2NK"}
{"name":"Shield Wall","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is a master of the art of weapon-and-shield combat. Forgoing the offensive abilities of a second weapon or the advantages of ranged weaponry, he proves the superiority of this most ancient and honourable of fighting styles. His shield seems to always be in the right position to block his foe&rsquo;s strike, leaving his target open for the inevitable counter.</p>\n<p>Effect: When armed with a shield, the character can re-roll one failed Evasion test to Parry an attack per round.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color: #ffffff; color: #202124; font-family: arial, sans-serif;\">Vikings!</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #202124; font-family: arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Raise the shield wall!</span><br style=\"color: #202124; font-family: arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\" /><span style=\"color: #202124; font-family: arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Hold the front line!</span><br style=\"color: #202124; font-family: arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\" /><span style=\"color: #202124; font-family: arial, sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\">Fight 'til death!</span></p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ambidextrous, Weapon Skill 40","aptitudes":"Defence, Weapon Skill","benefit":"re-roll one failed Evasion test","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"k2WiqIPLlS8l14XC"}
{"name":"Sprint","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte moves at great speeds, and when taking a Full Move action can move an extra number of metres equal to his Agility bonus. Additionally, whenever he takes a Run action, he may move double the normal distance. If he did so in the previous round, however, he suffers 1 level of Fatigue.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Agility, Fieldcraft","benefit":"Move more quickly in combat.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"NPnoh8dwZdMXb9Kg"}
{"name":"Step Aside","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Swaying his body out of the path of an attack, the Acolyte causes the shot to pass through thin air, or turns his blade mid-swing to deflect a blow. He can make an additional Evasion attempt (either a Dodge or a Parry) once per round. In effect, this gives him a second Reaction that can only be used for Dodge or Parry attempts, allowing two Dodges, two Parries, or a Dodge and a Parry in each turn. However, he can still only attempt a single Dodge or Parry against each individual attack.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 40, Dodge or Parry","aptitudes":"Agility, Defence","benefit":"Can make additional Dodge or Parry attempt.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"Um1PVuwajYjNVa4D"}
{"name":"Superior Chirurgeon","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s advanced medical training enables him to knit flesh with deft mastery, essential for treating combat casualties. His exceptional education in use of the Narthecium, Med-Slate, and supplemental drugs give his patients an enormous advantage. He gains a +20 bonus on all Medicae skill tests. When providing first aid, he ignores the penalties for Heavily Damaged patients and only suffers a &ndash;10 penalty for those suffering Critical damage.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 2 in the Medicae skill","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Fieldcraft","benefit":"Gain +20 to Medicae tests, bonuses to first  aid tests.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"hCbaXT0T64YYK4tg"}
{"name":"Target Selection","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s dread gaze marks out his chosen victim, and not even the riotous confusion of close combat interferes. He can shoot into melee with no penalty. If he also makes an Aim action beforehand, he prevents any chance of hitting friendly targets as well.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 50","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Finesse","benefit":"May shoot into melee without penalty.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"aPBdjlgzY3vDrHhK"}
{"name":"Thunder Charge","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte charges into combat using his body as an additional weapon. Driven by his rage and momentum, the impact of such a charge can knock foes flying or bring them to their knees. When he makes a Charge action, he can barrel through enemies to get to his target. The character makes an Opposed Strength test against each foe in his way (those who his movement would take him past or through). Each foe that loses the Opposed test is knocked Prone. After resolving these Opposed tests, the character&rsquo;s Charge action resolves against his original target as normal.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Strength 50","aptitudes":"Strength, Offence","benefit":"Break enemies with armoured charge.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"Vboes4hK6A0WelAE"}
{"name":"True Grit","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is able to shrug off wounds that would fell lesser men. Whenever he suffers Critical damage (after reduction for Armour and Toughness), reduce the amount by his Toughness bonus (to a minimum of 1 damage).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Toughness 40","aptitudes":"Toughness, Defence","benefit":"Reduce Critical damage taken.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"eciOrOABs4GrWFFW"}
{"name":"Two-Weapon Master","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has mastered the difficult ability of wielding a weapon in each hand, making him deadly both in personal and shortranged attacks. When armed with two single-handed weapons (such as a pistol or sword in either hand), he ignores the &ndash;20 penalty for Two-Weapon Fighting (see page 228).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 45, Ambidextrous, Ballistic Skill 40 or Weapon Skill 40, Two-Weapon Wielder (Melee, Ranged)","aptitudes":"Finesse, Offence","benefit":"No penalties when fighting with two single- handed weapons.","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"7ZVFMCl03lntkSrb"}
{"name":"Warp Lock","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has learned to swiftly cut himself off from the Warp to protect himself from harm. Once per game session, he may ignore the Psychic Phenomena he has rolled (including the Perils of the Warp result on Table 6&ndash;2: Psychic Phenomena, see page 196), completely negating its effects. Such rapid dislocation from the Warp, though, is stressful and traumatic to his mind. He suffers 1d5 Energy damage to the Head location (not reduced by Armour or Toughness) as a result, and cannot make any Focus Power tests or sustain other psychic powers until the beginning of his next turn.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Psy rating, Strong Minded, Willpower 50","aptitudes":"Willpower, Psyker","benefit":"Ignore Psychic Phenomenon once per session","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"LmfYVyjXLf4CX7nJ"}
{"name":"Hull Down","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte remains aware of his foes at all times in combat, carefully angling his vehicle or steed at each moment to present a narrower silhouette to all attackers, as well as taking the best advantage of any intervening terrain to gain cover. When the character takes a vehicle combat action with the Movement subtype, his vehicle or steed counts the value of its Size trait as being one lower for purposes of attack modifiers and the benefits of cover until the start of his next turn.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 2 in Survival or any Operate skill","aptitudes":"Agility, Fieldcraft","benefit":"Reduce size of vehicle while doing combat movement","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"B30npK640YFReYlH"}
{"name":"Push the Limit","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Whether through study, practice, or sheer intuition, the Acolyte is aware of the limits of his vehicle or steed, and knows how to push it to those limits and beyond. Although overtaxing a beast or executing wheel-tearing turns can provide a great advantage in combat or pursuit, a single wrong move can prove catastrophic, injuring the pilot or even ripping his vehicle apart. Once per round, the character may add +20 to an Operate test (or Survival test in the case of living steeds); however, if he fails the test by 4 or more degrees of failure, immediately roll 1d5 on Table 7&ndash;32: Motive Systems Critical Hit Effects on page 257 of the Dark Heresy Core Rulebook and apply the result. If he is riding a living mount, roll 1d5 on Table 7&ndash;18: Impact Critical Effects &ndash; Leg on page 239 of the Dark Heresy Core Rulebook and apply the result.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 2 in Survival or any Operate skill, Tech-Use","aptitudes":"Perception, Tech","benefit":"the Acolyte is aware of the limits of his vehicle or steed","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"OEqMmoyDhBSTW42g"}
{"name":"Weapon Intuition","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>In the prosecution of his duties against the alien, the Acolyte wields the most arcane and rare weapons the Adeptus Mechanicus can craft, and perhaps even takes up the very armaments of the xenos to better combat it. From years of experience, the character can quickly discern the firing mechanisms and balance of even the strangest weapons, regardless of its origin. The character reduces the penalty for using a weapon without the proper training by 10.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Exotic Weapon Training (Any)","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Finesse","benefit":"Use untrained weapons with -10 instead of -20","tier":3,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/3.png","effects":[],"_id":"NFhkkWchsxOG9Ism"}
